<concept id="id_2" class="- topic/topic concept/concept "><title class="- topic/title ">Install FFmpeg library</title><conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody "><p class="- topic/p ">To install the FFmpeg library:<ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">For macOS, use the following command with Homebrew: <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock ">$ brew install ffmpeg</codeblock></p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">For Linux, use the following command: <codeblock class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock ">sudo apt-get install ffmpeg</codeblock></p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">For Windows users: <ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Go to the <xref format="html" href="https://ffmpeg.org/download.html" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">FFmpeg download web page</xref>.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Download the package for Windows.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Add the path to the FFmpeg executable file to your PATH environment variable.</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Reactivate <ph conkeyref="name-variables/katalon-studio" class="- topic/ph "/> for this installation to take effect.</p></li></ol></p></li></ul></p><p class="- topic/p ">For more information on FFmpeg library, see: <xref href="https://ffmpeg.org/" scope="external" class="- topic/xref ">FFmpeg library</xref>.</p></conbody></concept>